In this question, you will prove by mathematical induction that the
following claim holds for all positive integers $n$.

\emph{Claim\begin{align*}1+2+2^2+2^3+\cdots+2^n=2^{n+1}-1.\end{align*}}

According to mathematical induction, two facts must be proven for the
claim to be true for all positive integers $n$. The first is the
following:

\emph{Fact 1: The claim holds for $n=1$; in other words, $1=2^{1}-1$.}

